Here are the steps to update Mozilla Firefox:

step 1: Open Mozilla Firefox and click on the menu button (three horizontal lines) in the top-

right corner of the window.

step 2:From the menu, go to "Help" and then click on "About Firefox".

step 3: In the "About Firefox" window, Firefox will check for updates and display the current 

version number. If an update is available, it will be downloaded and installed automatically.

If no update is available, you will see a message saying "Firefox is up to date".

step 4: Click on "Restart to update Firefox" to apply the updates and restart the browser.

 That's it! Mozilla Firefox will now be updated to the latest version.
